Conditional Statements

conditional statements is nothing but allows your program to make decion    s and exicute the program in diffrent blocks of code
depending on conditon is true or false


if {

}else{

}


Loops 

for loop : for loop in java is a type of a loop that repeats a code in set of times
(instalzition;condition;update)

for (int i = 1;i<=5;i++);

syso(i)

it will print the i 5 times

While Loop

a while loop in java its keep running as long as condition is true

int i =1;
while(i<=5){
syso(i)
i++;
}

Do While Loop

a do while loop garuntee the code run at least one time,even the condition is false

int i =1;

do{
syso(i);

i++;
}while(i<=5);


























